result.name: Genomic landscape of female lung adenocarcinoma
result.description: Comprehensive characterization of its genomic and immunological landscapes is crucial for cancer prevention and the development of precision therapy. Here, we report extensive genomic, transcriptomic, and immunological profiles of 117 female lung adenocarcinoma (XWFA), comprising 112 pairs of tumour-normal whole-exon sequencing (WES) profiles and 33 normal and 115 tumour mRNA-seq profiles.
